                "text": "If by \"secondary agent\" you mean the remote_a2a_a2atest agent available here, it’s a very small hello‑world test agent. Summary:\n\n- Behavior: it just returns \"hello world\" (intended as a demo). Example inputs that work: \"hi\", \"hello world\".\n- Input format: calls must use remote_a2a_a2atest.SendMessage with a message containing an array message.parts of text parts. Each part is an object with kind: \"text\" and text: \"<your string>\".\n- Limitations: text-only, no file handling, no complex actions or state — just a simple echo/hello response for testing.\n\nExample request payload:\n{\"message\":{\"parts\":[{\"kind\":\"text\",\"text\":\"hi\"}]}}\n\nExpected response: \"hello world\"\n\nIf you want, I can send a test message to that agent now. Which message should I pass?",
